definition[0]: the date stamped on a food product, after which it should not be sold
example[0]: a yoghurt two days past its sell-by date
definition[1]: a time beyond which something or someone is no longer interesting or useful
example[1]: This type of games console is starting to look well past its sell-by date.
definition[2]: the last date that a product, especially food, should be sold
example[2]: Some wine merchants have been selling the champagne past its sell-by date.
